Steps to build application
1. > npm install

2. > grunt build


npm install mocha@1.18.2 --save-devero

Create a public key on local

>ssh-keygen -t rsa 

Publish project to Heroky and gitHub. Go to Project folder

> git init
g
> git add .

> git commit -m "First committed"

> git remote add heroku git@heroku.com:myproject.git

> git remote add origin https://github.com/ScottWombat/myapp.git


> heroku login

> heroku create myproject --buildpack https://github.com/mbuchetics/heroku-buildpack-nodejs-grunt.git

> heroku keys:add

> git push heroku master

> git push origin master

> heroku ps:scale web=1

> heroku open

> heroku apps:open --app 'star2'

> heroku apps:info --app 'star2'


> heroku run node

********************************
>heroku run bash

>heroku logs

>heroku ps

>heroku restart 

*** bower ***
>bower init
>bower install
>bower uninstall <package>
>bower update <package>

>bower list

**************Curl*******************

curl -i -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d "{\"username\":\"xyz\",\"password\":\"xyz\"}" http://localhost:3000/login


